## Functional spec (per unit)

> Created when the project outgrows ad-hoc stories. Run `/ad-organize` to propose units.

- [Units](./units/)
  - Each unit holds: `stories.md` (functional), `decision-record.md` (ADR)
  - When a unit's `stories.md` exceeds ~500 lines, it splits into `story-001.md`, `story-002.md`, ... with `stories.md` as the index

## In-flight work

- [Iterations](./iterations/) — current development specs (`spec-YYYYMMDD-slug.md`)
- Deleted on PR merge; decisions transferred to the relevant ADR

## How to add a feature

```text
/ad-loop "describe the feature in one sentence"
```

Or step by step:

```text
/ad-story "describe the feature"        # → stories.md updated, ID returned
/ad-spec <story-id>                     # → iterations/spec-YYYYMMDD-slug.md
/ad-dev <spec-id>                       # → implementation
/ad-verify <spec-id>                    # → acceptance tests
/ad-validate <spec-id>                  # → gap report
/ad-pr <spec-id>                        # → PR opened
```
